Peter Nwachukwu, the husband of the late gospel singer, Osinachi Nwachukwu who was allegedly responsible for her death has reportedly escaped prison. Recall that a High Court in Abuja on June 3 remanded Nwachukwu at the Kuje Correctional facility, It was gathered that Nwachukwu was one of the suspects who escaped the facility during a terrorist attack last week Tuesday which led to the two persons while over 800 inmates were freed. A source from Dunamis International Gospel Center, Osinachi’s former Church, told Daily Post on Tuesday that he could not be found in the prison since the attack happened. According to him, a manhunt has been launched by security operatives in search of the suspect He said, “The day we heard of the prison break, we called the prison authorities to know the state of Mr. Nwachukwu but they were initially not forthcoming with the true situation. “But it was confirmed on Sunday that the man truly escaped from prison custody. “Manhunt has been launched on him at the moment. Security agencies have been briefed. POLL “They are also monitoring his bank account to see if there would be any transaction.”